<statement>
<image width="33%" pi:generated="problems/images/mom-1057112-1.png"/><p>
Suppose a = 6 and A = 20 degrees. Calculate:</p>
<p>
b = <input type="text" style="width:25ch" name="qn1000" id="qn1000" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 1 of 3" class="text"/></p>
<p>
c = <input type="text" style="width:25ch" name="qn1001" id="qn1001" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 2 of 3" class="text"/></p>
<p>
B = <input type="text" style="width:25ch" name="qn1002" id="qn1002" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 3 of 3" class="text"/> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place.  Give angles in <em>degrees</em>
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>16.5</li><li>17.5</li><li>70.0</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p>For the length of the other leg,</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\tan{{\left({20}\right)}}}=\frac{{6}}{{b}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}=\frac{{6}}{{\tan{{\left({20}\right)}}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}\approx{16.484864516728}\approx{16.5}</m>.</p>
<p>For the third side</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={6}^{{2}}+{16.484864516728}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={36}+{271.75075813487}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={307.75075813487}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}=\sqrt{{{307.75075813487}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{17.542826400979}\approx{17.5}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{B}={180}^{\circ}-{90}^{\circ}-{20}^{\circ}\approx{70}^{\circ}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>